doc.after: A constant speed propeller is a variable pitch propeller which automatically changes its blade pitch in order to maintain a chosen rotational speed The power delivered is revs torque and the propeller operation places emphasis on torque The operation better suits modern engines particularly supercharged and gas turbine types
